patients with previously treated KRAS G12D

537
00:33:00.860 --> 00:33:02.180
non-small cell lung cancer.

538
00:33:03.120 --> 00:33:04.280
Here are my disclosures.

539
00:33:06.460 --> 00:33:10.240
RAS is a GTPase that transitions between an inactive

540
00:33:10.320 --> 00:33:12.960
GDP-bound off state to a

541
00:33:13.020 --> 00:33:16.889
GTP-bound on state. Under normal

542
00:33:16.900 --> 00:33:20.540
conditions, the system is tightly regulated, with RAS on

543
00:33:20.580 --> 00:33:22.580
proteins controlling cell growth.

544
00:33:23.360 --> 00:33:27.010
With RAS cancer mutations, there's excessive RAS on signaling

545
00:33:27.440 --> 00:33:29.380
that drives uncontrolled cell growth.

546
00:33:30.260 --> 00:33:34.240
KRAS mutations are numerous, but mainly concentrated on

547
00:33:34.340 --> 00:33:37.700
G12, G13, and Q61.

548
00:33:38.640 --> 00:33:42.260
KRAS G12D is the most common oncogenic RAS mutation

549
00:33:42.640 --> 00:33:46.020
in human tumors and lacks an approved targeted treatment.

550
00:33:46.760 --> 00:33:50.380
As shown in the figure, 61,000 new patients per year

551
00:33:50.720 --> 00:33:54.600
in the United States are diagnosed with KRAS G12D cancers.

552
00:33:55.140 --> 00:33:58.900
This includes 40% of pancreatic adenocarcinoma,

553
00:33:59.480 --> 00:34:02.420
15% of colorectal cancer, and

554
00:34:02.620 --> 00:34:06.400
4% of non-small cell lung cancer, which is about the same

555
00:34:06.460 --> 00:34:10.321
frequency in non-small cell lung cancer as ALK fusion non-small cell lung

556
00:34:10.380 --> 00:34:10.801
cancer.

557
00:34:11.761 --> 00:34:15.490
KRAS G12D mutations in non-small cell lung cancer

558
00:34:15.980 --> 00:34:19.620
are often associated with a never or light smoking status,

559
00:34:20.120 --> 00:34:23.380
low tumor mutational burden, and low PDL1

560
00:34:23.420 --> 00:34:26.830
expression compared to non-G12D KRAS mutant

561
00:34:26.920 --> 00:34:30.500
tumors. Treatment options for patients with KRAS

562
00:34:30.600 --> 00:34:33.930
G12D non-small cell lung cancer that's advanced or

563
00:34:34.000 --> 00:34:37.761
metastatic after progression on platinum-based chemotherapy

564
00:34:38.080 --> 00:34:40.690
and immune checkpoint inhibitors are limited.

565
00:34:41.190 --> 00:34:44.930
The standard of care in this setting is docetaxel with

566
00:34:44.960 --> 00:34:48.700
consideration of ramucirumab that can be toxic and has low

567
00:34:48.781 --> 00:34:52.660
response rates, a median progression-free survival in the three to

568
00:34:52.720 --> 00:34:56.700
four and a half month range, and limited overall survival.

569
00:34:56.740 --> 00:35:00.480
This illustrates a large unmet need for targeted therapies in

570
00:35:00.520 --> 00:35:04.080
KRAS G12D mutated non-small cell lung cancer.

571
00:35:05.380 --> 00:35:09.340
Zoldonrasib is an oral mutant selective covalent inhibitor

572
00:35:09.780 --> 00:35:13.600
targeting the on active GTP-bound state of RAS

573
00:35:13.640 --> 00:35:17.420
G12D. Promising preliminary safety and

574
00:35:17.500 --> 00:35:21.140
clinical activity has previously been reported in pancreatic

575
00:35:21.240 --> 00:35:25.040
adenocarcinoma and non-small cell lung cancer, and

576
00:35:25.220 --> 00:35:29.120
zoldonrasib has breakthrough FDA designation based on

577
00:35:29.180 --> 00:35:32.140
these results in non-small cell lung cancer. Dr.

578
00:35:32.260 --> 00:35:36.060
Arbor presented the early data from this study last

579
00:35:36.140 --> 00:35:39.620
year, and here I present more patients and a longer duration of

580
00:35:39.660 --> 00:35:40.260
follow-up.

581
00:35:41.300 --> 00:35:45.120
Zoldonrasib's mechanism of action is shown here in the

582
00:35:45.180 --> 00:35:49.060
cartoon. It binds inside the cell to cyclophilin A, a protein

583
00:35:49.120 --> 00:35:53.110
abundant in cells, forms a binary complex, and then has

584
00:35:53.140 --> 00:35:56.700
non-covalent binding with RAS on, and then in

585
00:35:56.760 --> 00:36:00.420
G12D, binds to 12 aspartic acid. The

586
00:36:00.460 --> 00:36:03.720
resulting tri-complex sterically occludes RAF

587
00:36:03.760 --> 00:36:07.570
interaction and inhibits RAS on oncogenic activity

588
00:36:07.940 --> 00:36:09.300
and downstream signaling.

589
00:36:10.740 --> 00:36:14.600
Zoldonrasib drives deep and durable regressions in KRAS

590
00:36:14.660 --> 00:36:18.480
G12D non-small cell lung cancer preclinical models in

591
00:36:18.900 --> 00:36:22.880
vivo. Here I show deep responses in the waterfall plot in these

592
00:36:22.900 --> 00:36:26.760
preclinical xenograft models, and these responses were durable,

593
00:36:26.860 --> 00:36:30.080
as you can see, in the opposite Kaplan-Meier curve for

594
00:36:30.600 --> 00:36:31.200
xenografts,

595
00:36:32.180 --> 00:36:35.300
with prolonged progression-free survival and these durable

596
00:36:35.360 --> 00:36:39.064
responsesIn part based on this exciting

597
00:36:39.144 --> 00:36:42.944
preclinical data, RMC9805001

598
00:36:43.384 --> 00:36:46.604
Phase 1 study was initiated. Here I present arm A

599
00:36:46.784 --> 00:36:50.564
zoldanrasib monotherapy. Key eligibility criteria

600
00:36:50.624 --> 00:36:54.264
include patients with advanced solid tumors with KRAS

601
00:36:54.364 --> 00:36:57.884
G12D mutations. They have to have had progressed on prior

602
00:36:57.944 --> 00:37:01.754
standard therapy appropriate for tumor type and stage, good

603
00:37:01.844 --> 00:37:05.754
performance status, zero to one, and no active brain metastases,

604
00:37:06.204 --> 00:37:09.124
although patients with stable, asymptomatic, treated brain

605
00:37:09.164 --> 00:37:11.364
metastases were allowed on study.

606
00:37:11.944 --> 00:37:15.604
Key endpoints include safety and tolerability and anti-tumor

607
00:37:15.704 --> 00:37:18.164
